src_text: Vuvekisi Khabinete yi amukela vuvekisi bya R3 wa tibiliyoni ku suka eka Khamphani ya Mimovha ya Ford ku ya eka Feme ya le Silverton, ePitori, Gauten Vuvekisi lebyi byi ta vuyerisa hi ku tumbuluxa mitirho yo kongoma na yo ka yi nga kongomi hikokwalaho ka ku languteriwa ka ntlakuko wa andziso wa modele ya wona ya Ford Range Vuvekisi byolebyo byi tiyisisa ntirho lowu hi ya ka emahlweni hi wu endla tanihi mfumo eku kuriseni ka ikhonomi na le ku lulamiseni ka mitlhontlho ya vupfumalantirh Hi ku tirhisa xikimi xa xinavetisi xa mfumo xa Rwa tibiliyoni eka Phurogireme ya Nhluvukiso na Andziso wa vumaki bya Mimovha, R2wa tibiliyoni ta vuvekisi byo ka byi nga ri bya mfumo byi humesiwil Lebyi byi katsa xitiviso hi Toyota ku endla timodele ta vona tintshwa ta Toyota Hilux na Fortuner tanihi xiphemu xa vuvekisi bya Rwa tibiliyon Nakambe, BMW yi kunguhata ku aka garaji yo lungisela mimovha ya ximanguva lawa ya R6 wa tibiliyon Khamphani ya Matiko hinkwawo ya Mimovha ya le Beijing yi kunguhata ku vekisa R11 wa tibiliyoni eka feme ya vumaki bya mimovha eAfrika-Dzonga Nguva ya Xibalo ya 2017 Khabinete yi hundzisela ku khensa eka vahakeri va xibalo hinkwavo lava se va tlheriseke tifomo to hlela xikweleti xa vona xa xibalo ta lembe ra xibalo ra 2016/12.

src_text: Zimbabwe Khabinete yi seketela ku nghenelela hi Phuresidente Jacob Zuma, eka ntirho wa yena tanihi Mutshamaxitulu wa Muganga wa Nhluvukiso wa Matiko ya le Dzongeni wa Afrika (SADC) hi ku angula eka xiyimo xa MaZimbabw U rhumerile Varhumiwa vo Hlawuleka, Holobye wa Vusirheleri na Khale ka Masocha, Ma Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula na Holobye wa Xiyenge xa Vuhlayiseki bya Tiko, Adv Bongani Bong Va ta hlangana na Phuresidente Robert Mugabe na Vuthu ra Vusirheleri ra le Zimbaby Endzhaku ka sweswo, va ta hlamuselanyana Phuresidente wa le Angola Jo o Louren o tanihi ntirho wa yena wa Mutshamaxitulu eka xirho xa SADC eka Tipolotiki, Vusirheleri na Vuhlayisek Hofisi ya Phuresidente yi ta tivisa leswi ya ka emahlweni eka mhaka leyi Square Kilometre Array (SKA) Khabinete yi amukela ku humelela ka nhluvukiso wa vanhu na wa ikhonomi loku kumekeke ku suka eka vuvekisi lebyi a byi kongomiwile eka nhluvukiso wa vanhu eka rhijini ya SKA ya Afrika-Dzong Miganga leyi nga kusuhi na ndhawu SKA yi ya emahlweni yi vuyeriwa hi tiphurojeke ta dyondzo na vuleteri to antswa, vuvekisi eka mabindzu lamatsongo na ku tlakuka ka swivandlanene swa
trg_text: Cabinet congratulates France as the preferred host of the 2023 Rugby World Cup and thanks government s delegation, headed by Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa, Sport and Recreation Minister Thulas Nxesi and the South African Rugby Union, for the work done in promoting South Africa s bid to host the even Cabinet congratulates Minister Pandor, who was awarded the Outstanding Educator Awar The award was presented to Minister Pandor by the Chancellor of the University of South Africa, former President Thabo Mbek The Outstanding Educator Award, one of four categories, acknowledges the contribution of any outstanding educator who has excelled in or advanced teaching, learning, skills development and/or research in their area of expertis Cabinet commends the work done by the South African Astronomical Observatory, which is part of the Wide Angle Search for Planets consortium of planet hunters who have detected three new planet Cabinet congratulates the participants and winners of the 2017 Govan Mbeki Awards, which honour those in the construction sector who have excelled in the delivery of house The awards come as the country continues to celebrate the delivery of over million houses and subsidies since 199.

src_text: Swiviko swa ku humelela swa kotara ya vumbirhi hi matirheloswa 2017/18 Khabinete yi hlamuseriwile hi swiviko swa ku humelela swa kotara ya vumbirhi hi matirhelo swa 2017/18 (Mawuwana ku fika Ndzati 2017) hi mitlawa hinkwayo ya ntlhan Leswi swi vumba xiphemu xa nandzeleriso na nkambelo wo angarhela wa Khabinete wa Phurogireme ya Nghingiriko lowu kumekeke ku suka eka Rimba ra swa Maqhinga ra Nkarhi wa le Xikarhi (MTSF) wa 2014 ku fika 2012.

src_text: Ndzawulo ya Makunguhatelo, Kambisisa Matirhelo no Hlela na Tikomiti ta Tlawa wa Vaholobye va ta fambisa mbhurisano na vuhangalasi bya mahungu ku hlamusela hi xitalo ku humelela ka swiviko lesw GCIS yi ta fambisa mbhurisano na vuhangalasamahungunyingi na ku hangalasa xedulu eka wwgoza hi ku famba ka nkarhi Ku antswisiwa ka pfhumba ra makumelo ya kherefu na manyikelo ya tikherefu Khabinete yi hlamuseriwile hi xiviko xa nhluvukiso eka masimekelo ya Maavanyiselo ya Khoto ya Vumbiwa ku nyika tikherefu eka rhijisitara ra vavhot Khabinete yi tsakisiwile hi ku landzelela ko helela ka swiviko swa nhluvukiso swa le ndzhaku ka tin'hweti tin'wana na tin'wana ta tsevu leswi rhumeriweke eka Khoto ya Vumbiw Ku fikela sweswi Khomixini ya Nhlawulo yo Tiyimela (IEC), hi ku tirhisana na tiejensi tin'wana ta mfumo, yi kumile ku humelela ka kwalomu ka 75% eku hlengeleteni ka tikherefu ta lava va nga tshukaka va ri vavhot Khabinete yi hlamuseriwile hi nongonoko lowu kunguhatiweke wa SAPO ku pfuna lava nga riki na tikherefu ta laha va tshamaka kon Khabinete yi tsakisiwile hi nhluvukiso na ku tirhisana loku endliweke hi SAPO, na IEC tiejensi tin'wana ta mfumo eku nyikeni ka phurojeke ya tikheref Khabinete yi ya emahlweni yi kombela volavo va nga si antswisaka tikherefu ta vona ku endla tano hi nkarhi lowu taka wa vhiki ra ntsariso wa vavhoti hi Nyenyankul Mitlangu leyi Taka10.
trg_text: The Department of Planning, Monitoring and Evaluation and the Ministerial Cluster Committees will conduct media briefings to unpack the progress of these report The GCIS will coordinate the media briefings and publish the schedule on wwgoza in due course Update on address harvesting initiative and assignment of addresses Cabinet was briefed on the progress report on the implementation of the Constitutional Court Judgement to assign addresses to the voters rol Cabinet appreciated the full compliance with the six monthly progress reports submitted to the Constitutional Cour To date the Independent Electoral Commission (IEC), working with other state agencies has attained almost 75% success in collecting the addresses of potential voter Cabinet was also briefed on the planned programme by the SAPO to assist those who do not have physical addresse Cabinet is pleased with the progress and the collaborative work conducted by SAPO, the IEC and other state agencies on the assignment of addresses projec Cabinet further calls on those who have not updated their addresses to do so during the next voter registration week in March 2018.

src_text: Nhlengeletano ya vumune ya Khomixini ya Matikomambirhi ya Afrika-Dzonga na Botswana (BNC)1 Phuresidente Zuma u ta sungula riendzo ra ntirho ku nghenelela na ku rhangela Nhlengeletano ya Vumune ya Matikomambirhi ya Afrika-Dzonga na Botswana BNC leyi nga ta khomeriwa eGaborone, eBotswana hi Ravuntlhanu, 17 Hukuri 201 Afrika-Dzonga na Botswana ya hlangana lembe na lembe eka levhele ya Tihloko ta Matiko eka rimba ra BNC ku xopaxopa ntirhisano wa matiko ha vumbirhi na ku kanela timhaka ta ntsakelo wo fanaMatiko lamambirhi ya tiphina hi vuxaka bya xinghana lebyi vumbiweke hi ku hlangana ka swa mfuwo na ku va kusuhi na ku kusuh Ya tirhisana eka timhaka to talanyana leti katsaka, vutleketli, bindzu na vuvekisi, rihanyu, timhaka ta swa mbango sswAfrika-Dzonga hi rin'wana ra vatirhisani va bindzu lavakulu va Botswana, ku na tikhamphani to hlaya ta Afrika-Dzonga ti nga ri tingani leti tirhaka eka tiko rer Riendzo ra Phuresidente wa Angola1 Phuresidente Zuma u ta rhurhela Muchaviseki, Phuresidente wa Riphabliki ra Angola, Jo o Louren o, eka Riendzo ra Mfumo ra matimu eAfrika-Dzonga ku suka hi ti 23 Hukuri 2017.
trg_text: Fourth session of the South Africa-Botswana Binational Commission (BNC)1 President Jacob Zuma will undertake a working visit to participate in and co-chair the Fourth Session of the South Africa-Botswana BNC to be held in Gaborone, Botswana on Friday, 17 November 201 South Africa and Botswana meet annually at the level of the Heads of State within the framework of the BNC to review bilateral cooperation and discuss issues of common interestThe two countries enjoy cordial relations which are informed by cultural ties and geographical proximit They cooperate on a number of issues including,

src_text: Leri ku ta va ku ri Riendzo ra Mfumo ra yena ro sungula etikweni ra hina endzhaku ka loko a vekiwile exitulwiniMatiko lamambirhi ya na ku hlangana ka xinghana na ka matimu kusukela eka masiku ya ku lwela ntshuxeko loko Anglola ri rhurhele na ku seketela tinhenha ta ku lwela ntshuxeko ta Afrika-Dzonga eka tikamba to hambanahambana etikweni leriyaNtirhisano wa ikhonomi na bindzu exikarhi ka matiko lamambirhi wu kurile swinene, ku fikela laha Afrika-Dzonga ri nga muringani wa bindzu wo rhanga wa Angola eka tikonkul Tikhamphani ta Afrika-Dzonga to tala ti le ku endleni ka bindzu eAngola eka tisekitara to hambanahambana ku katsa na vuako, migodi, tindlu, nxaviso xin'wexin'we, swakudya na swakunwa, tihotela na ku tiphina, vukorhokeri bya swa vutshunguri na byo bangHi nkarhi wa riendzo ra yena, Phuresidente Louren ou u ta tlhela a fambisa Dyondzo hi Ravuntlhanu, 24 Hukuri 2017 eka Muako wa OR Tambo ePitor Masiku ya 16 ya ku Lwisana na madzolonga1 Khabinete yi hlangana na MaAfrika-Dzonga hinkwawo lawa ya teka goza ro lwa na ku xanisiwa ka vavasati na vanaPfhumba ra Masiku ya 16 yo Lwisana na Madzolonga ehenhla ka Vavasati na Vana ri ta va kona exikarhi ka ti 25 Hukuri na 10 N'wendzamhala 2017.
trg_text: historical and fraternal ties dating back from the days of the liberation struggle when Angola housed and supported South African liberation cadres in various camps in that countryTrade and economic cooperation between the two countries has grown substantially, to the extent that South Africa is Angola s number one trading partner on the continen Many South African companies are conducting business in Angola in a variety of sectors including construction, mining, housing, retail, food and beverages, hotels and leisure, banking and medical serviceDuring his visit Jo o Louren o will also host a Lecture on 24 November 2017 at OR Tambo Building in Pretori 16 Days of Activism1 Cabinet joins all South Africans who are taking a stand against women and child abuseThe 16 Days of Activism for No Violence against Women and Children campaign is taking place between 25 November and 10 December 2017.
